Since the Shah was our ally in a VERY hot fracture zone between NATO and the Soviets, we had to keep friendly relations with him.
<br />

<br />
###
<br />

<br />
To do otherwwise would have given the soviets control of the entire middle east and its oil.  They were already in Afghanistan and sponsoring any and all rebels including and especially Kohemeni.
<br />

<br />
Right after the fall of the Shah, Kohemenis people turned Iran into a killing field and took up the exact same tactics to control the population that had turned people against the Shah.  They ruthlessly killed off his remaining supporters AND people that had helped them oust him all in the name of god.
<br />

<br />
Worse the torture and abuse was spread to even more commoners as new islamic laws were passed to further repress the populace.  Islamic clerics who were not sunni or sunni and not sworn alliegence to Kohemeni were rounded up and shot.
<br />

<br />
###
<br />

<br />
To say the Shah was "our Crony" is laughable.  No one in that area was a crony to the US.  We had to play our hand close to our chest there and make allies of leaders whom we would rather not have had to.
<br />

<br />
If anything we were the Shah's crony.<br />
