Before the reformation, it was illegal for one christian to charge interest on loaning money to another (which Shakespeare rendered as <span style="font-style: italic">neither a borrower, nor a lender be</span> in Hamlet). Therefore, the only semi-legal finance industry was jewish (because they were not christian). The word usury originally meant charging any interest at all.  Deut 23:19-20, Jeremiah 15:10-14 among others were used as the biblical basis for the ban under the catholic church.
<br />

<br />
The markets for money, stocks and insurance came about at that time. The loss of control of the catholic church allowed those industries to thrive. And these markets perish when a nation turns its back on capitalism and turns instead to sharia.
<br />

